author: Karlee Weinmann
title: Job Creation Fund burns through initial $24 million allocation
text:
Home / Brief / Job Creation Fund burns through initial $24 million allocation Job Creation Fund burns through initial $24 million allocation By: Karlee Weinmann September 2, 2015 1:00 pm 0 A popular program designed to support job-creating expansions by Minnesota companies doled out the entire $24 million allocation that got it started last year. The Minnesota Department of Employment and Economic Development said Tuesday that its Job Creation Fund had distributed the full $24 million that the 2013 Legislature funneled into it.
